Now, we combine two close FB states. As these modes have an amplitude and phase structure, we can combine them using in phase and out of phase composition. The FB state located to the left is called ϕ
L [see Fig. 3(a)] and the one located to the right is called ϕ
R [see Fig. 3(b)]. We could generate infinite linear combinations depending on the coefficients in front of these states: αϕ
L + βϕ
R, with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
